# Airborne pollen variability and meteorological relationships in Greece

**EGU General Assembly 2026**
**Poster presentation**

**Presenter:** Georgios Roditis
**Affiliation:** National and Kapodistrian University of Athens, National Observatory of Athens
**Contact:** groditis@noa.gr

---

##Overview

This poster presents an analysis of airborne pollen concentrations and their relationships with meteorological conditions across three regions in Greece: Athens, Thessaloniki, and Finokalia.

The study combines pollen observations from Hirst-type volumetric samplers with ERA5 reanalysis data and in-situ meteorological station observations.

---

## Study sites

| Site | Environment | Pollen data coverage |
|---|---|---|
| Athens | Urban | 15 Apr 2022 – 15 Apr 2023 |
| Thessaloniki | Urban / coastal | 2016–2021, excluding 2018 |
| Finokalia | Background / coastal | 22 Feb 2018 – 28 May 2018 |

---

## Main focus

- Pollen seasonality and taxonomic composition
- Pollen–meteorology relationships
- Lagged correlations between pollen and meteorological variables
- ERA5–station comparison for meteorological consistency

